The underlying data file for this application is available from the National Archive of Criminal Justice Data. With this application users can explore the characteristics of domestic violence victims, including demographic information of the victim (age, sex, and race), victim injury, and the victim-offender relationship. The current release of Easy Access to NIBRS: Victims of Domestic Violence is based on incidents reported in 2010 from law enforcement agencies in 33 states. Users should be aware of the fact that the NIBRS data capture an unknown portion of the domestic violence victims known to law enforcement within a State (i.e., some agencies within a State do not report their information to the FBI).</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>victims</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>victims-of-domestic-violence</dcat:keyword>     <foaf:homepage
